load ../infoflow-redact-provenance.maude

--- Redaction does not launder read provenance. The record customer has public
--- fields idF and statusF and an operator-only field ssnF. A derivedFrom fact
--- marks customer as derived from a confidential operator resource read. The key
--- property: dropping fields cannot remove the read provenance, so a redacted
--- egress of confidential-read-derived data leaks even when only public fields are
--- kept -- the concrete twin of the checker purely-additive redact refinement.

--- ============================ COVERAGE (leak reachable) =====================

--- Coverage, THE under-taint that must be caught: keep only the public fields idF
--- and statusF, but the record was derived from a confidential read
--- derivedFrom operator. Released to a public sink it STILL leaks -- redaction
--- dropped the secret field but not the read provenance. This is the leak
--- reproduced in the checker before the fix.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-REDACT-PROVENANCE :
  deleg(emptyR)
  field(customer, idF, noP) field(customer, statusF, noP)
  derivedFrom(customer, operator)
  sink(out, noP)
  release(customer, (idF ; statusF), out)
  =>* C:Cfg leak .

--- Coverage: keeping the secret FIELD leaks to a public sink even with public
--- provenance -- the field-level case, consistent with infoflow-redaction.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-REDACT-PROVENANCE :
  deleg(emptyR)
  field(customer, idF, noP) field(customer, ssnF, operator)
  sink(out, noP)
  release(customer, (idF ; ssnF), out)
  =>* C:Cfg leak .

--- ============================ BITE (no leak) ================================

--- Bite: redaction HELPS when there is no confidential provenance. Dropping the
--- secret field with NO derivedFrom -- a public-provenance record, or a declassified
--- read, contributes noP -- released to a public sink does NOT leak. No solution.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-REDACT-PROVENANCE :
  deleg(emptyR)
  field(customer, idF, noP) field(customer, statusF, noP) field(customer, ssnF, operator)
  sink(out, noP)
  release(customer, (idF ; statusF), out)
  =>* leak RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: a CLEARED sink may receive even confidential-provenance data. The record
--- is derived from an operator read but released to an operator-cleared sink with
--- reader set operator; the sink dominates the provenance, so no leak. No solution.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-REDACT-PROVENANCE :
  deleg(emptyR)
  field(customer, idF, noP) field(customer, statusF, noP)
  derivedFrom(customer, operator)
  sink(out, operator)
  release(customer, (idF ; statusF), out)
  =>* leak RESIDUAL:Cfg .
